<br>
The GMs on FV, in what I have observed, look for small groups to pop events on, instead of the PC Loot Bum-Rush that happens on traditional servers.<br>
<br>
Moreover, the smaller events DO seem connected (like they have a common plot or thread) and are not 'stock' events...<br>
<br>
The GMs at Verant are (very obviously) not professional Paper and Pencil GMs (and, yes, there are professional paler and pencil GMs out there, who do make money at it). Regardless, they are getting better at running events, plotting, and figuring out how to work with large groups and the entire dynamic of large group events.<br>
<br>
Since the best way to get good at plotting is to use smaller gorups of players, i APPLAUD them for not having meat-market 50-100 person 'scavenger hunt' events.<br>
<br>
These 'scavenger hunt' and 'scripted' events (like that piece of shit Lanys T'Vyl thing they did) are frequently CRAP, have no real plot or interaction with the players. It is a 'run on rails' event... the players have no input or say in the outcome.<br>
<br>
At least the GMs here seem to trust us, the players, and I like that. <p>Nakath<BR>
